The Chelsea Football Club has mourned one of its former players, Christain Atsu, who passed on due to the earthquake in Turkey. They made this known via its Facebook page on Saturday. ALSO READ: Missing Ghanaian footballer, Atsu, found dead rubble of Turkey earthquake Condoling with the family of Atsu, they said, “Everyone at Chelsea Football Club is devastated to learn of the tragic passing of our former player, Christian Atsu. Our thoughts go out to his family and friends.” 